ANTHRAX - BULGARIA: (SHUMEN) BOVINE
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 22 Aug 2014
Source: Focus [in Bulgarian, machine transl., edited]
http://www.focus-news.net/news/2014/08/22/1957222/probata-ot-shumenskoto-selo-zagoriche-e-polozhitelna-za-antraks.html


According to the results of laboratory tests, the sample from the dead calf in the village of Zagoriche [Shumen oblast] tested positive for anthrax. This was announced on Radio "Focus" quoting Shumen's Dr. Katya Raykinska, director of the Regional Directorate of Food Safety. In addition, the carcass has been incinerated and the farm disinfected. All susceptible livestock -- 600 cattle and 900 sheep -- have been vaccinated. "A timely response requires that all hazards are avoided. Samples were taken on 13 Aug [2014]; control measures were immediately put into effect; and on 20 Aug [2014] we received a positive record of anthrax," said Dr. Katya Raykinska. She noted that at this stage there were no other signs of suspected infection in the field.

[Byline: Ivelin Ivanov]

