[For Zagoriche in northeast Bulgaria, go to: http://www.fallingrain.com/world/BU/54/Zagoriche.html.

Frankly, it is unusual to see anthrax in a calf, so I suspect the affected animal was a yearling.

Shumen seems to be the oblast for anthrax in Bulgaria. It suffered an ovine outbreak in 2013, and 3 bovine outbreaks in 2012. It is presumably this consistent history that has persuaded the oblast veterinarians to vaccinate the sheep and cattle in Zagoriche this time. Latterly livestock vaccination in Bulgaria has not been done since 2009. As the disease is truly sporadic in Bulgaria, this is understandable. But we need to remember Kyriakus Polydoru's successful strategy for Cyprus that at this point annual vaccination should be tightly targeted at the areas were there are outbreaks occurring, while just keeping a sharp eye out for unexpected deaths elsewhere. (Thanks to Sabine for this report.) - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2714789,9061.]
